description:
The Graduate Women in Business (GWIB) organization strives to address the unique challenges and issues faced by women in today's business world. GWIB's mission is to provide a supportive network of current members, alumni, and members of the Madison community;
To provide members space to discuss and learn about relevant issues facing women in business; and
To advance the education and promotion of women in business.

The mission of the Hmong American Student Association is to:
1. Promote higher education;
2. Serve as a bridge between students, community leaders, and scholars with the Hmong community and the broader American community;
3. Address the concerns and needs of students and the Hmong community such as Hmong Human Rights, Students’ Rights and Civil Rights;
4. Provide leadership opportunities for aspiring students;
5. Serve as a resource for students;
6. Serve as a channel to develop, display, and recognize the talents and creativity of the students.
